What is the difference between OOP and POP?

-> OOP, refers to Object Oriented Programming and its deals with objects 
and their properties.
-> POP, refers to Procedural Oriented Programming and its deals with programs and functions. 

-> An object-oriented program uses the Bottom-up approach. 
-> A procedure-oriented program uses the Top-down approach.

